An antique car dealer sources rare vintage cars for a mechanic to restore and sell. The dealer can source cars from different years ranging from 1920 to 1980. The mechanic has a preference for cars from certain years due to the uniqueness and value of cars from those years. The years preferred by the mechanic form a set M.

The set M = {1925, 1930, 1935, 1940, 1945, 1950, 1955, 1960, 1965, 1970, 1975, 1980}

The dealer, in his current sourcing trip, found cars from the years that form set D.

The set D = {1930, 1945, 1950, 1960, 1970, 1980}

Find the supremum and infimum of the set D with respect to the set M. 

Also, determine if there exist any years in set D which are also the supremum or infimum in set M.
